*.json
!baseline-latest.json
!stage-*.json
*.log

# Per-run perf bench outputs written by e2e/perf-bench.spec.ts → PERF_LABEL.
# Always machine-local. Headless-Chrome timings on a 4-core Linux runner
# look nothing like timings on an M-series Mac, so committing one
# machine's numbers as a shared "baseline" was misleading — it can't be
# used as a hard threshold across hosts. Devs record their own local
# baseline with `pnpm test:perf:baseline` and diff against it during
# optimization work. CI compares its own runs across commits via the
# uploaded artifact (.github/workflows/test-perf.yml).
*/

# CPU profile dumps (PERF_TRACE=1). Always local, never committed.
*.trace.json
*.cpuprofile
